////Biceps Tendon - Rupture

Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 06 - Labrum & Ribbons of Shoulder MRI
When I select the radio button 'Finding'
Then 'Finding' dropdown menu is enabled
When I select 'Biceps Tendon' from the Finding dropdown
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled

And 'Rupture' radio button is enabled
And 'Degeneration' radio button is enabled
And 'Tendinitis' radio button is enabled
And 'Pulley-lesion' radio button is enabled
And 'SLAP lesion type IV' radio button is enabled

And 'Serial number' input field is enabled
And 'Image number' input field is enabled
And 'Import reference image' image uploader field is enabled

And 'Outline' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Rupture' radio button
Then 'Retraction in mm' input field is enabled
And 'Retracted tendon stump on the biceps anchor' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Retracted tendon stump on the biceps anchor' checkbox
Then 'Intra-articular entrapment' checkbox is enabled
